   <abstract>This report is one in a series of studies by CDF examining state policies and practices in child care and early childhood education. It focuses on conducting child care market rate surveys and establishing reimbursement policies that can support quality child care. The "Market Rates" concept is explained as well as the "Market Driven" approach to the purchase of publicly funded child care services as included in federal initiatives.</abstract>
